\\theta = \\frac{1}{\\cos \\theta}$, and $\\csc \\theta = \\frac{1}{\\sin \\theta}$.\n\\[\\frac{1}{\\sin^2 \\theta} - \\frac{1}{\\cos^2 \\theta} - \\frac{\\cos^2 \\theta}{\\sin^2 \\theta} - \\frac{\\sin^2 \\theta}{\\cos^2 \\theta} - \\frac{\\cos^2 \\theta}{\\sin^2 \\theta} - \\frac{\\sin^2 \\theta}{\\cos^2 \\theta} = -3\\]\nSimplifying further, we get:\n\\[\\frac{1}{\\sin^2 \\theta} - \\frac{1}{\\cos^2 \\theta} - 2\\left(\\frac{\\cos^2 \\theta}{\\sin^2 \\theta} + \\frac{\\sin^2 \\theta}{\\cos^2 \\theta}\\right) = -3\\]\nSince $\\frac{\\cos^2 \\theta}{\\sin^2 \\theta} = \\cot^2 \\theta$ and $\\frac{\\sin^2 \\theta}{\\cos^2 \\theta} = \\tan^2 \\theta$, we have:\n\\[\\frac{1}{\\sin^2 \\theta} - \\frac{1}{\\cos^2 \\theta} - 2(\\tan^2 \\theta + \\cot^2 \\theta) = -3\\]\nUsing the identity $\\tan^2 \\theta + 1 = \\sec^2 \\theta$ and $\\cot^2 \\theta + 1 = \\csc^2 \\theta$, we get:\n\\[\\frac{1}{\\sin^2 \\theta} - \\frac{1}{\\cos^2 \\theta} - 2(\\sec^2 \\theta - 1 + \\csc^2 \\theta - 1) = -3\\]\n\\[\\frac{1}{\\sin^2 \\theta} - \\frac{1}{\\cos^2 \\theta} - 2(\\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta - 2) = -3\\]\n\\[\\frac{1}{\\sin^2 \\theta} - \\frac{1}{\\cos^2 \\theta} - 2(\\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta - 2) = -3\\]\nUsing the identities $\\frac{1}{\\sin^2 \\theta} = \\csc^2 \\theta$ and $\\frac{1}{\\cos^2 \\theta} = \\sec^2 \\theta$, we get:\n\\[\\csc^2 \\theta - \\sec^2 \\theta - 2(\\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta - 2) = -3\\]\n\\[\\csc^2 \\theta - \\sec^2 \\theta - 2\\sec^2 \\theta - 2\\csc^2 \\theta + 4 = -3\\]\n\\[-|\\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta| + 4 = -3\\]\nSince $|\\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta| = \\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta$, we have:\n\\[-(\\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta) + 4 = -3\\]\n\\[-(\\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta) + 4 = -3\\]\n\\[-(\\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta) = -7\\]\n\\[\\sec^2 \\theta + \\csc^2 \\theta = 7\\]\nSince $\\sec^2 \\theta = 1 + \\tan^2 \\theta$ and $\\csc^2 \\theta = 1 + \\cot^2 \\theta$, we have:\n\\[1 + \\tan^2 \\theta 